			</Contributors>
			<Body>
				<Text Type="text">
					&lt;p&gt;Drinking beer alone does not cause you to get a big belly, it's the amount food that goes along with it. People usually drink beer in the evening, and tend to eat a lot of food at the same time. And this is great and dandy, but what people forget about is that they eat late (here combined with drinking beer so even more calories), and then go straight to bed. The body does not have a chance to break down all of these calories, and instead all of this excess fat is being stored.&lt;/p&gt;

					&lt;p&gt;In short, the beer alone does not cause the fat, it's the food that goes along with it.&lt;/p&gt;

