			<Body>
				<Text Type="text">
					&lt;p&gt;Anxiolytics is too broad of a term to address. Alcohol is actually frequently considered an &lt;a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Anxiolytic#Alcohol" rel="nofollow"&gt;anxiolytic&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

					&lt;p&gt;Antidepressants, on the other hand, certainly &lt;strong&gt;can have adverse effects&lt;/strong&gt; when mixed with alcohol.  As far as drug interactions go, it will largely vary on the drug--without more information it is really impossible to say for sure what the answer is in your case.&lt;/p&gt;

					&lt;p&gt;However, on a more broad note, the use of alcohol is generally perceived as counterproductive while on antidepressants.  &lt;strong&gt;Alcohol can contribute to depression&lt;/strong&gt;, so it is generally advised to be avoided while taking antidepressants. For more information, see this article: &lt;a href="http://www.nhs.uk/chq/Pages/863.aspx?CategoryID=73" rel="nofollow"&gt;Can I drink alcohol if I'm taking antidepressants?&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

					&lt;p&gt;Hope this helps!&lt;/p&gt;

				</Text>
			</Body>
