			<Body>
				<Text Type="text">
					&lt;p&gt;Beer is fermented typically (but not exclusively) via yeast.  When live beer yeast, actually a fungus, is present, it creates a hostile environment for (potentially harmful) bacteria reducing their prevalence.  Therefore, fresh beer could be considered a safer alternative to say, river water.&lt;/p&gt;

