			<Contributors>
				<OwnerUserId>37</OwnerUserId>
				<LastEditorUserId>-1</LastEditorUserId>
			</Contributors>
			<Body>
				<Text Type="text">
					&lt;p&gt;There's very little hard research on the healthful benefits of beer, though there is some observational research on both beer and (as Jens mentioned in &lt;a href="https://alcohol.stackexchange.com/a/4731/37"&gt;his answer&lt;/a&gt;) on the benefits of moderate levels of alcohol in general.  &lt;/p&gt;

					&lt;p&gt;It's also been noted that there beer has a number of ingredients that are generally believed or known to be healthy, including vitamins, fiber, silicon, and others.  &lt;/p&gt;

					&lt;p&gt;So, while I wouldn't base a diet on it, moderate consumption of beer is at least anecdotally a reasonably healthy habit in which to imbibe.   &lt;/p&gt;

				</Text>
			</Body>
