			<Body>
				<Text Type="text">
					&lt;p&gt;I have friends who has gout who still drinks beer, BUT you should be aware of your alcohol limit before you get the worst out of the scenario. Wine should be the best way for you to get the booze out of the drink. So watch out of the alcohol content before doing so, its no that I'm encouraging you to do so, but any limit due to your condition would not lead to NOT doing so. Better yet consult your specialist if you still have the urge to engage in drinking beer/wine.&lt;/p&gt;

